==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scrimp
<hw>Scrimp</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Scrimped</conjf> <pr>(?; 215)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Scrimping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. Dan.
<ets>skrumpe</ets>, G. <ets>schrumpfen</ets>, D. <ets>krimpen</ets>. Cf.
<er>Shrimp</er>, <er>Shrink</er>.]</ety> <def>To make too small or
short; to limit or straiten; to put on short allowance; to scant; to
contract; to shorten; <as>as, to <ex>scrimp</ex> the pattern of a
coat</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- To economize. Scrimp and save. Economize and save the money not
spent. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrimp</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scrimp
<hw>Scrimp</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Short; scanty; curtailed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrimp</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Scrimp
<hw>Scrimp</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A pinching miser; a niggard.</def>
<mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrimping</ent>⟦br⟧
